00:32:47.305 --> 00:32:51.570
<v Maya>We are building a digital id and a digital superego and setting them loose in our homes.</v>

303
00:32:52.103 --> 00:33:00.570
<v Daniel>We can't wrap this up without talking about the risks. We have a final section here on the ethical landscape. And honestly, reading through some of this stuff is genuinely terrifying.</v>

304
00:33:00.670 --> 00:33:10.318
<v Maya>It is. The stakes are incredibly high. Because if we succeed, if we actually build agents with accurate mental world models, we are building machines that could know us better than we know ourselves.</v>

305
00:33:10.498 --> 00:33:15.502
<v Daniel>Privacy is the big obvious one. If the AI knows my intent, then it knows my secrets.</v>

306
00:33:16.022 --> 00:33:26.287
<v Maya>It knows your habits, your weaknesses, your desires, your political leanings, your deviations from your normal routine. The paper mentions federated learning as a potential solution.</v>

